                                                                        My Favorite Products                                                            



													Details							

  Last Updated: 29 October 2015 29 October 2015 

This page is a collection of my favorite supplements. These are products that I have used or do currently use as part of my "Better Health" program or have gotten very good reports from others.¬† I welcome any comments or suggestions you may have. I am always open to learning about new products that may be better than some of those that I currently consider to be at the top of my list. I expect this list will change over time, but do think these are good options.
I have attempted to break them down into categories such as Antimicrobials, Detoxification, and so on.The products listed below are NOT presented in any specific priority. Always consult with your healthcare provider before starting anything listed on this page.

Antimicrobials

Beyond Balance MC-BB-1, MC-BAB-1, MC-BAB-2, MC-BAB-3, MC-BAR-1, IMN-R (formerly Immune Restore), IMN-V (formerly ImmunoVira), MC-REGENATO-1, MC-PROTA-Z, ENV-N, and Parazomin 

Beyond Balance offers comprehensive herbal blends that may be helpful for people dealing with Lyme disease.¬† Some of their products include MC-BB-1, MC-BAR-1, MC-BAB-1, MC-BAB-2, MC-BAB-3, IMN-R (formerly Immune Restore), IMN-V (formerly ImmunoVira), MC-REGENATO-1, MC-PROTA-Z, ENV-NM, Parazomin, and others.¬† I personally have been on protocols incorporating these products and have seen very positive shifts.¬† More details on these products can be found here. ¬†Custom protocols can be developed by Susan McCamish CTN via Better Health as discussed in my blog entry here.Sources: Beyond Balance

Supreme Nutrition Morinda Supreme, Vital Guard Supreme, Melia Supreme, and Golden Thread Supreme

Some of my absolute favorite products come from Supreme Nutrition.¬† Morinda Supreme has been helpful for both Babesia and Bartonella.¬† Vital Guard Supreme may be useful for Borrelia.¬† Melia Supreme is very broad-spectrum (as are many of the antimicrobials from Supreme Nutrition), and Golden Thread Supreme may be helpful for those dealing with Protomyxzoa rheumatica.Sources: Supreme Nutrition

Maypa Herbals Formula-L, Formula-Bart, Formula-Bab, and Formula-Green

The Maypa Herbals products were formulated by an herbalist and medical intuitive.¬† They are a unique combination of herbs that I have found very helpful.¬† I used these products for almost a full year with good results.¬† I find that they can be very effective but do not seem to product the same Herxheimer response that many other options do.Sources: Maypa Herbals


NutraMedix Samento, Cumanda, Banderol, Enula, Mora, Lakato, Hottuynia


NutraMedix Samento, Cumanda, Banderol, Enula, Mora, Lakato, and Hottuynia are excellent herbal preparations that can be helpful to inhibit the growth and presence of various microbes. I personally have used Samento and have alternated between Cumanda and Banderol on regular cycles. Enula and Mora may be a good option for intracellular infections such as Babesia.¬† I have used them both.If one is looking for options other than antibiotics, the "Cowden Protocol" which is based on NutraMedix products is a very well-planned treatment option that you may wish to consider in conjunction with your healthcare provider.Sources: Immune Matrix, LLC , NutraMedix Additional Information: NutraMedix

BioPure Quintessence

BioPure Quintessence is as close to the "Buhner protocol in a bottle" that I have seen. ¬†This product is one that I have used along the way for dealing with Lyme and related infections.¬† It is one of the key components of the Klinghardt Lyme Cocktail discussed here.Sources: BioPure

Systemic Formulas TVIVI

Systemic Formulas TVIVI¬†is one of my go-to remedies for viral issues.
Sources: Systemic Formulas

Seagate Olive Leaf

Seagate Olive Leaf may be¬†very useful in dealing with viral issues.
Sources: iHerb.com

Immune Modulation and Support

Myco Formulas Immune Defense

One of my more recent favorites is Myco Formulas Immune Defense.¬† It is a blend of many mushrooms that may support the immune system and fortify the body's response to various microbes.
Sources: Myco Formulas


Transfer Factor LymPlus and Transfer Factor PlasMyc


Transfer Factor LymPlus is a transfer factor product that may be useful for people with Lyme and co-infections as well as some of the major viruses such as EBV, CMV, and HHV6. I started taking this at a dosage of 1 capsule at bedtime for the first month and then increased to 2 capsules each night at bedtime. Transfer Factor PlasMyc¬†is another excellent product from the same company that supports the body against numerous microbial attacks, including Mycoplasma.Sources: Immune Matrix, LLC Additional Information: Researched Nutritionals

Researched Nutritionals Transfer Factor Multi-Immune

Researched Nutritionals offers Transfer Factor Multi-Immune which may be a good option for supporting immune function and addressing various microbial infestations.¬† I think that many of us focus so much on Lyme that we overlook all of the viruses that are also impacting our health.¬† Having a product like Transfer Factor Multi-Immune in a protocol may be a very wise way to support the immune system to address things that are not always considered.
Additional Information: Researched Nutritionals¬†

General Detoxification

Beyond Balance TOX-EASE, TOX-EASE GL, TOX-EASE II 

TOX-EASE, TOX-EASE GL, and TOX-EASE II are blends of numerous herbs that may support optimal detoxification. ¬†I have used these product several times during my recovery and find them to be very useful options in supporting the body's ability to detoxify. More details on these products can be found here. ¬†Custom protocols can be developed by Susan McCamish CTN via¬†Better Health as discussed in my blog entry¬†here.Sources: Beyond Balance


Pekana Homeopathics (apo-HEPAT, RENELIX, ITIRES)


Pekana Homeopathics (apo-HEPAT, RENELIX, ITIRES) are some of the best homeopathic products I have used to support drainage and detoxification.¬† They are for the liver, kidneys, and lymphatic system respectively.¬† They may be a good base for supporting the body's ability to detoxify.¬† In my opinion, everyone with Lyme disease should talk with their doctor about adding these into their foundational program. I've also had excellent results with TOXEX and MUNDIPUR which are both from Pekana.¬† The only caveat here is that at times, apo-Hepat, can be too provoking and may be best replaced with Syntrion SyDetox using SyDetox, RENELIX, and ITIRES.Sources: Forrest Health Additional Information: BioResource, Inc.


Healthforce Intestinal Drawing Formula 


Healthforce Intestinal Drawing Formula is a powerful binder for many different toxins. It includes Zeolite, Charcoal, Bentonite Clay, and other detoxification-supporting substances.Sources: iHerb.com

BioRay LiverLife

BioRay LiverLife is an excellent product for supporting the liver, a primary organ of detoxification.Sources: iHerb.com

Eclectic Red Root

Eclectic Red Root is a product I have used to support movement of the lymphatics and detoxification. ¬†It was excellent for me when I was detoxing heavily from the use of GcMAF therapy.Sources: iHerb.com

BioPure Chlorella

BioPure Chlorella has been a staple in my recovery. ¬†I often chewed 30-40 tablets about 30-45 minutes before a meal. ¬† There are so many benefits to chlorella including that it may be helpful for detoxification of heavy metals. ¬†BioPure carries a high quality chlorella product that is what I personally use. ¬†Jarrow carries a number of chlorella products as well such as¬†Yaeyama Chlorella.Sources: BioPure

PectaSol-C

PectaSol-C is a fiber or binder that assists the body in the process of detoxification.Sources: Econugenics

Heavy Metal Detoxification
Please see my Heavy Metals page for more detail on my experience with heavy metal detoxification.


Longevity Plus Zeo Gold


Longevity Plus Zeo Gold supports detoxification. ¬†It is a product I use daily mixed in water with¬†Bio En'R-Gy C. ¬†  Sources: Longevity Plus


ACZ Nano


ACZ Nano is a zeolite spray that I have used extensively over the past couple of years.¬† More details on this product can be found in my article entitled Total Body Detox: A Novel Approach to Lowering Total Body Burden.
Sources: Longevity Plus¬†Additional Information: Results RNA
Note: There has been a lot of discussion on whether or not the aluminum contained in zeolite products is a potential problem or not. ¬†I do personally like ACZ Nano, but it is known that zeolites contain aluminum. ¬†Many suggest that the aluminum does not remain behind in the body, but others disagree. Do your research and discuss with your doctor before deciding whether or not zeolite is right for you.

